- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of dependently typed languages and the category of contexts associated with them. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper mentions design criteria for user-centric library design. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as there is no mention of machine learning in the abstract or title, but the paper may touch on some concepts related to category theory which is used in some areas of machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category as the paper does not seem to focus on data structures or algorithms specifically.
